    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make UK-US trade-deal transparent to Parliament and the public without secrecy",
        "additional_details": "Nick Dearden, director of the trade campaign group Global Justice Now, told HuffPost UK it \u201cisn\u2019t standard practice to insist on lengthy periods of secrecy even after a deal has been signed\u201d. \r\n\r\nHe said while there was no \u201cgold standard\u201d, the talks between Washington and Brussels would be more open, adding: \u201cThis five-year secrecy clause may be what the US administration wants, but it\u2019s up to the UK to say set out its own criteria.",
        "background": "Make all aspects of the UK-US trade deal negotiations transparent to Parliament and the British Public and do not sign up to five years secrecy after the negotiations start or come into force.",
